

Sprint Backlog

Sprint 1:
User Story 1: As a user, I want to be able to create tasks to organize my work.
    -Design the frontend interface for the "Create Task" form.
    -Develop the "Create Task" form with input validations.
    -Connect the backend functionality to the "Create Task" form.
    -Refactor code for improved readability and maintainability.
    -Conduct testing on the "Create Task" form to identify and fix any errors or bugs.


Sprint 2:
User Story 2: As a user, I want to be able to update tasks to modify their details as needed.
    -Design the "Edit Task" option and corresponding form.
    -Develop the "Edit Task" form and implement necessary validations.
    -Add a checkbox that updates the status of the task when clicked.
    -Connect the backend functionality to the "Edit Task" form.
    -Refactor the code for improved readability and maintainability.
    -Conduct testing on the "Edit Task" form to identify and fix any errors or bugs.


Sprint 3:
User Story 3: As a user, I want to be able to delete tasks to keep my task list organized.
    -Design the "Delete Task" option.
    -Develop the "Delete Task" functionality and implement necessary validations.
    -Connect the backend to the "Delete Task" functionality.
    -Refactor the code for improved readability and maintainability.
    -Conduct testing on the "Edit Task" form to identify and fix any errors or bugs.


Sprint 4:
User Story 4: As a user, I want to be able to mark my tasks as done to track my progress.
    -Design the task list to include a functional checkbox for each task.
    -Implement functionality so that clicking the checkbox applies strikethrough text and marks the task as completed.
    -Enhance visual design elements to better differentiate each column in the task list.
    -Refactor the code for improved readability and maintainability.
    -Test the task completion functionality to identify and resolve any errors or bugs.


